title: 'Excellent quality for the price'
body: The note book is unbelievable quality for the price . You can blindly go for it . Remember you cannot select the book cover and it's not the same what is displayed. I got a different one too but luckily the design was even better from what is shown in the pictures . It's good for everyday use like taking notes, practicing etc. Might not be good for drawing/ colouring in sketch pen, brush pen etc. I m using it with dark ink fountain pen hence bit of ghosting is there but definitely not a deal breaker. The paper is very smooth and pleasant, the pen just glides on it . Great value for money.

title: 'More pros than cons. Value for money.'
body: Gorgeous notebook! It's nice, big and sturdy. Larger than A5 and shorter in length than A4, which is exactly the size I prefer for journalling. The lines are not too close to each other like in other school notebooks and that's a bonus for me. The top got a little smushed during the transit but it's not a big issue. The ink/writing shows on the backside but it's not a deal breaker for me because once you write on the backside, the visibility of the first side isn't prominent. Overall a great purchase!
